  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Raising standards of care for children with epilepsy in Ghana, Tanzania, Uganda, Kenya by scaling up sustainable Paediatric Epilepsy Training (PET) targeted at high-level health workers</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Scale-up existing PET Africa programme and ensure sustainability by increasing capacity of PET trainers in Ghana, Tanzania, Uganda and Kenya, with the aim of raising the standard of care for children with epilepsy/seizures in those countries by building capacity of paediatricians to correctly diagnose and treat children appropriately</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project is implemented by British Paediatric Neurology Association, Paediatric Neurology Development Association of Southern Africa, Muhimbili University of Health &amp; Allied Sciences, Tanzania and Paediatric Association of Tanzania, Mulago Hospital &amp; Makerere University College of Health Sciences, Komfo Anokye Teaching Hospital and Aga Khan University Kenya.</narrative>
  </description>
